item.title: Compiler help!
item.dc:creator: @Gh0st_Jr Gh0st Jr
item.description:
@Gh0st_Jr wrote:

well… with compilers you need to download the JKD 6 update 6 or w\e. so once you have that then you need to right click your compiler and click edit. Once youve done that then you will see where the compiler is gonna look for JKD 6 update (w\e) so if you dont have that file, lets just say it looks like this. @echo off title (your compiler name here) "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_04\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java pause and it wont work but you have JKD 6 update 6 then you change the 4 to a 6. so it will look like this @echo off title (your compiler name here) "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_06\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java pause

  • hope this helps,
    Gh0st Jr
